values: She finally got here from Miami, and in our reconciliation i got to ride her all day. Yes i have been in my bike all day! My scanner also got here safely, so now i can get back to posting pictures.

Finally a town with good show! I just found out that Arctic Monkey and We are Scientists are going to be in town June 4.
I am so THERE!

Today i got a little reminder of why i left everything behind. Why i left my family, my friends, and everything i knew. All of that to move to a city where i had only been once for three days and where i didnt know anyone or anything for that matter. For a while i had forgotten why i chose to move from Miami FL all the way to Tempe AZ. Some of my friends would tell me, "all the way there for a job?!", but now i see that they will never understand, that actually not even i do sometimes. The reason? Well when do you have the chance to have a job in which you really help, in which you really know that you are saving a life? I was given that chance and i when for it. You see some of us want to be heros or even more than that, but when given the opportunity to just do your best and help, we run away. Is it because we only want the opportunity that gets recognition? or the one where you really help? I chose to help, even if it meant leaving all behind. But the main reason are on this charts Deaths From Diseases of the Heart

Cardiovascular Disease (CVD) Deaths vs. Cancer Deaths by Age

And these are the things that i'll be working with. They look weird, but to my eyes they have a different meaning.
Some people are just lucky, for the rest of us it takes planning.
From my album, my Stops project (i hate them).
All i ever do now is say Goodbye, or get ready for that time!
Anyone up for some sushi? I really want to go eat some.

Is sad when you have to say bye to those who really showed to care. I am glad i got to meet you guys and will never forget any of you. Special thanks for the friendship of: Aiesha Isaac Summer Ryan Amanda Laura Peter Chun Case Elena and of course Alexis, Yen-Chih, and Dimitris, but those go without saying. Sincce this list goes on and on, i will just say thanks to everyone in Gainesville who in one way or another has made an impact in my life.

Today I am leaving to Orlando for two day and then to Gainesville after untill Saturday. I am going to see some of my friends for the last time, since everyone is moving or graduating and going back home. Lets hope for a great time.
